# Both-theme component build standard

**Binding (Andrew 2026-06-07):** design and verify **light + dark in the same build slice**. No separate theming pass.

## Rules

1. **Done = both themes verified** — a component or page is not complete until it looks correct with `[data-theme=light]` and `[data-theme=dark]` on `<html>`.
2. **Theme via tokens only** — use design tokens / CSS variables / `[data-theme]` (`src/styles/tokens.css`, `src/styles/shadcn-theme.css`). Semantic classes (`bg-card`, `text-foreground`) over raw hex.
3. **`data-theme="dark"` is source of truth** — never rely on OS-only `prefers-color-scheme` or Tailwind `dark:` that does not follow `[data-theme=dark]` (app uses `@custom-variant dark` keyed to `data-theme`).
4. **Whiteboard** — Excalidraw `theme` must follow **app-selected** theme, not OS-only (`useExcalidrawThemeFromSystem` → app hook). **TU-12**.

